content.description: Hand and fist crack at the right side of the west face.  The easiest walkoff comes down to the left of the start of this route.

climbs.name: Excuuuse Me
climbs.fa: Steve Parker, Dave and Sheryl Haber, 9/1994

content.description: Reachy steep start rightward and upward via a shallow dihedral.  Continue vertically as the thin crack straightens.  Upon reaching helpful horizontals, slant up and right to finish.  This route is located on the SW corner of the rock.
content.location: Walk off partway toward the backside, then descend to climber's left to zigzag back down to ground, touching down about 20 ft left of the start of Not The Clean Crack.

climbs.name: Blame It On Cain
climbs.fa: Dave and Sheryl Haber, Steve Parker, 9/1994

content.description: Reachy and pumpy start to go up an overhanging bulge located to adjacent right of Excuuuse Me.  Fun jugs rest of the way to the top.

climbs.name: Ben's Magic Weenie
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Tucker Tech & Mark Synott

content.description:
Face climbing on steep plates to thinner face.

Four lead bolts protect the route.

Can be led from Blame it on Cain by traversing in from that route. Â Pro available in this crack approach.
content.protection: 4 lead bolts. Stoppers and cams to 1" if coming in from the left via Blame it on Cain.
content.location: Just right of the crack line Blame it on Cain.
